julie seltzer the clayman institute for gender research skip to main content standford university the clayman institute for gender research the clayman institute for gender research home programs news strategic focus events about research fellowships library media center gender news no news found events february 29 2012 7 00pm women's torah female scribes artists and visionaries you are here home people julie seltzer julie seltzer scribe women's torah project julie seltzer is a soferet scribe a hebrew calligrapher who writes sacred texts on parchment she is one of a few women who work as soferets and describes scribing as an art that fuses so much of who she is and what she loves torah hebrew art ritual meditation seltzer has previously worked in the contemporary jewish museum in sf theatre jewish education and most recently as baker at the isabella freedman jewish retreat center in falls village ct she is a team member of the seattle women's torah project donate make a donation social links facebook twitter youtube scribd contact serra house 589 capistrano way stanford ca 94305 8640 map 650 723 1994 gender email stanford edu
